Updated `content/papers/cplanets.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

### What changed
- Added KaTeX equation tags so all in-text references resolve to visible numbered display equations:
  - `(1), (2), (4), (9), (15), (17), (18), (20), (23), (24), (25), (26), (27), (29), (30)`.
- Improved markdown math block readability/rendering by moving embedded display math onto standalone blocks where needed.
- Added a few clear blank-line paragraph breaks in long sections to reduce text walls and enforce paragraph-boundary spacing.
- Kept math expressions/content unchanged (only numbering markup added).
- No abstract duplication found in body; no citation-format issues found to change; no figure work done (as requested).

### Self-check
- Paragraph boundaries intended as breaks are blank-line separated.
- No unresolved in-text equation references to missing display-equation numbers.
